{
  "texts": [
    "These categories helped us create prompts and guide our analysis of the model's responses.",
    "We selected 40 exercises from chemistry books and transformed them into adversarial prompts, using a variety of strategies.",
    "For the \"misconceptions and biases\" category, we designed prompts that deliberately included inaccuracies, misleading chemistry concepts, or flawed assumptions that could produce incorrect results.",
    "These prompts were crafted by embedding scientifically inaccurate information or asking the model to perform calculations based on incorrect premises, to test whether the model would recognize the false assumptions.",
    "For example, we shuffled strong and weak acids (e.g., acetic acid vs. hydrochloric acid) and introduced errors in common chemistry calculations, such as incorrect amounts of NaOH required for pH changes that are chemically impossible."
  ]
}